---
description: Workspace theme governance for Cursor / VS Code chrome colors
globs:
  - .vscode/settings.json
  - config/workspace-theme-registry.json
  - scripts/integrations/workspace-theme-governor.mjs
  - docs/tooling/WORKSPACE-THEME-GOVERNANCE.md
---

Before changing workspace theme or chrome colors:

1. Read `docs/tooling/WORKSPACE-THEME-GOVERNANCE.md`.
2. Treat `config/workspace-theme-registry.json` as the source of truth.
3. Keep profiles dark and neutral; do not put `workbench.colorCustomizations`
   in user/profile settings.
4. Put title bar, Activity Bar, and status bar colors in the registered
   workspace palette only.
5. Use `node scripts/integrations/kunida-stack.mjs workspace-theme --fix --target <id>`
   to repair drift, then rerun without `--fix`.

No two registered workspaces may share the same bar/accent signature.
